message.content:
One wondered if this greater awareness of the physical cosmos might
with time instill the reverence which, on Earth, nature inspires,
especially when one reflected that the rockets over which Mr. Bron's
board presided had it in their power permanently to warp the
solar system. True enough, such ultimate weapons had not been
used in the last the few wars, but it seemed very probable
that they would be in the next one, Moon and her
allies being more inferior than formerly to W.C.U. in the
weapons pronounced conventional.
